div.p:
Boohs of Account required by a Merchant.— Journal; ledger;
                    cash-book; bills payable, or book of his acceptances; bills receivable, or book
                    of bills on other merchants, to be paid to his order; order-book, with copies of
                    all orders received; bought-book, or book for bills of parcels delivered in;
                    letter-book, having copies of all letters to the correspondents of the house;
                    invoice-book, or account of goods shipped or sold; account of sales-book;
                    insurance policy-book; petty journal, or book for such occasional entries as are
                    not inserted in the other books; petty cashbook, or book of petty disburse.
